page.content: IN MY SPARE TIME I LIKE TO PRACTICE SWIMMING AS OFTEN AS I CAN.I GO TO FISHBURN BATHS AND I TRAVEL BY BUS WHICH COSTS 8p SO IT IS CHEAP BECAUSE IT IS ONLY A MILE AWAY.IT IS DIFFICULT TO DESCRIBE HOW TO ACTUALLY SWIM.TO SWIM YOU SWING ONE ARM ROUND AND THEN THE OTHER BUT BOTH ARMS HAVE TO SWING AT DIFFERENT TIMES OTHERWISE YOU WOULD SINK.YOU MUST KEEP YOUR FINGERS TOGETHER ON EACH HAND, AND YOU KICK YOUR LEGS UP AND DOWN IF YOU DO ALL THAT TOGETHER IT MAKES A STROKE CALLED FRONT CRAWL.ALSO IN FRONT CRAWL YOU MUST PUT YOUR HEAD IN OR YOUR BODY ISN'T STRAIGHT AND HALF OF YOUR BODY IS LOPSIDED AND YOU SINK.THERE ARE MANY DIFFERENT AWARDS TO GET FOR SWIMMING AND MANY DIFFERENT TYPES OF STROKES, FOR EXAMPLE, BREAST STROKE AND BUTTERFLY.IN BUTTERFLY YOU SWING BOTH ARMS AT THE SAME TIME.S. FISHBURN
